reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I needed
reviews.reviewText: I got this to try and simplify my life a little. I have both USB type A adapters, USB Type C adapters, and adapters that have Both Type A and Type C USB ports. I was getting tired of keeping track and storing all these adapters. So, I decided it would be easer to go with straight C as much as possible. It’s newer technology and most things are going that way anyway. I could have used a cheap adapter that would change it from Type A to Type C, but I am leery of using adapters of any kind. If the cable starts having issues, it’s one more thing I must troubleshoot when figuring out what the issue is. If there is no adapter, and the cable starts having issues, it’s most likely the cable, and I can just swap cables to test it out. Again, trying to simplify my life. One of the challenges of using third party cables is getting one that is also MFi certified. This is important for two reasons. The first and probably most important is that non-MFi cables can run hot and potentially overheat the device, which can cause damage. Second MFi devices support data transfer. When I want to connect my phone to a computer, I do not want to have to remember which cable works for data transfer and which one does not. Once again, simplicity. This cable supports data transfer and doesn’t overheat my device. The cables look to be of good quality, so I think they will last for a while. Overall, I like these cables.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars You get what you pay for
reviews.reviewText: These are charging cables for lightning devices. They work.I would not trust them for data transfer. I would not expect them to last a long time under heavy usage,However, they do work and charge my kids devices. The kids loose these cables at an astonishing rate, so having a decent set of cables for an affordable price is a good thing.I would absolutely recommend these if you have a family full of forgetful squirrels.Would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lasted about a month
reviews.reviewText: I give cords out to my young children to do their torture testing. Usually cords last about a week, So these lasting over that is pretty impressive. Though I wish someone could crack the code and make a cable that last forever. I tested these for power output before handing them off to my kids and they indeed charge at the rated 20w. Over all there are a good value. And I'll buy them again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works just fine
reviews.reviewText: Full disclosure: I got this product through Amazon's Vine programI have an old iphone 7 I couldn't unlock because I forgot the passcode. To erase / reset it, I needed to connect it to my laptop; and that required this type of cable.As you can see from pic, you get three cables nicely packaged in a ziplock pouch. They have the same feel as any other Apple cable but I've read about how non-original cables can have issues re: transfer of data. Fortunately, I did not encounter any such issue here. I followed Apple's directions on how to reset the phone and everything worked just as it was supposed to. Once finished, the phone's screen indicated that it was also charging through the cable ( as expected ).I got this product specifically for this purpose. And it worked just fine.Very pleased.
